      <p class="lede first">Most Pinterest accounts are flat because of a keyword problem wearing a design costume. The pins look fine. Nobody is searching the words on them.</p>

      <p>This planner fixes the order of operations. You choose the keyword first, then you design the pin — never the reverse.</p>

      <p>It's the worksheet system from inside Pinterest Foundations™, extracted and given away. Fill it once per content pillar and you'll never stare at a blank pin description again.</p>

