        <h2>Four steps, in order</h2>
      </div>

      <ol class="list">
        <li><strong>Start with seed words.</strong> The obvious phrases for your niche. Ten is plenty.</li>
        <li><strong>Type each into the Pinterest search bar</strong> and record what autocomplete suggests. Those suggestions are real searches.</li>
        <li><strong>Click the guided search tiles</strong> across the top of the results for more related keywords.</li>
        <li><strong>Aim for 30-50 keywords</strong> to start. Favor specific, longer phrases over broad ones.</li>
      </ol>

      <div class="box tip">
        <div class="tag"><span class="g">✦</span> Verify as you go</div>
        <p>If a keyword shows up in Pinterest's autocomplete, real people search it — keep it. If nothing comes up, skip it. However clever the phrase is.</p>
